sequenceDiagram
    title Loop Progress Report — Data Flow

    participant ORCH as ORCHESTRATOR
    participant INNER as INNER_AGENT
    participant PEER as PEER_AGENT
    participant KERNEL as kernel.py
    participant LEDGER as improvement-ledger.md
    participant SURVEY as retrospectives/
    participant REPORT as generate_report.py
    participant CHART as progress_YYYYMMDD.png

    note over ORCH: Stage 1 — Orientation
    ORCH->>LEDGER: Read Section 1 (score trajectory for target)
    LEDGER-->>ORCH: Prior eval scores, KEEP/DISCARD history, running best
    ORCH->>LEDGER: Read Section 2 (unresolved survey friction items)
    LEDGER-->>ORCH: Prior friction items + whether each was resolved
    ORCH->>LEDGER: Read Section 3 (north star completion rate trend)
    LEDGER-->>ORCH: Completion rate per session, trend direction

    note over ORCH: Stage 2 — Execute cycle
    ORCH->>INNER: task.assigned (strategy packet informed by ledger)
    INNER->>KERNEL: emit friction events during work
    INNER->>PEER: eval result via kernel bus
    PEER->>PEER: run skill-improvement-eval independently
    PEER-->>ORCH: eval.result (KEEP/DISCARD + score delta)

    note over ORCH,PEER: Stage 4.2 — Surveys (both agents)
    INNER->>SURVEY: Save survey_[DATE]_INNER_AGENT.md
    PEER->>SURVEY: Save survey_[DATE]_PEER_AGENT.md
    ORCH->>SURVEY: Save survey_[DATE]_ORCHESTRATOR.md

    note over ORCH: Stage 4.6 — Test Registry Update
    ORCH->>ORCH: Close scenario file, update registry.md row

    note over ORCH: Stage 4.7 — Update Improvement Ledger
    ORCH->>LEDGER: Append Section 1 row (date, cycle_id, target, baseline, after, delta, verdict, change_summary)
    SURVEY-->>ORCH: Read friction items from all 3 surveys
    ORCH->>LEDGER: Append Section 2 rows (survey_id, agent, friction_item, action, file, change, eval_delta, outcome)
    KERNEL-->>ORCH: friction_events_total from post_run_metrics
    ORCH->>LEDGER: Append Section 3 row (session, completion_rate, human_interventions, friction_events_total)
    ORCH->>KERNEL: emit ledger_updated event

    note over ORCH: Optional chart update (after KEEP, or on user request)
    ORCH->>REPORT: python3 generate_report.py --project-dir ... --plugin-dir ...
    REPORT->>LEDGER: Parse Section 1 (eval score progression)
    REPORT->>LEDGER: Parse Section 2 (survey-to-action trace)
    REPORT->>LEDGER: Parse Section 3 (north star metric log)
    REPORT->>CHART: Save progress_YYYYMMDD_HHMM.png
    REPORT-->>ORCH: Text summary (top hits by delta, completion rate trend)
    ORCH-->>User: "Chart updated at reports/progress_[TS].png. Want to see the summary?"

    note over ORCH: Next cycle orientation
    ORCH->>LEDGER: Read again — trajectory now includes this cycle's row
    note right of LEDGER: KEEP row: score trending up<br/>DISCARD row: this approach did not work<br/>Flat step line: try different hypothesis
